    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PDU Session Resource Modify Indication Handler Implementation\n\n### Summary\nThe `ngap_gNB_handle_ng_ENDC_pdusession_modification_confirm` function in the gNB NGAP module was implemented as a stub that only logged a warning message. When the gNB received a PDUSessionResourceModifyIndication message from the AMF during EN-DC operations, the function would return immediately without processing the PDU session modification requests, causing PDU session establishment failures and RRC connection drops.\n\nThe root cause was an incomplete implementation that did not parse the incoming NGAP message or forward the PDU session modification information to the RRC layer. This fix provides a complete implementation that properly handles the PDUSessionResourceModifyIndication message according to 3GPP TS 38.413 specification.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_handlers.c`: Replaced stub implementation with complete handler that parses AMF UE NGAP ID, RAN UE NGAP ID, and PDUSessionResourceModifyListModInd, then forwards the information to RRC via ITTI messaging.\n"
}